CLOSEU.S. District Court Judge Dominic Lanza said the Arizona Constitution requires initiative campaigns to collect signatures from supporters in person.
(Photo: Charlie Leight/The Republic)A federal judge rejected a request by two ballot measure campaigns to collect petition signatures from voters online as an alternative to dispatching volunteers with clipboards during a pandemic.
But U.S. District Court Judge Dominic Lanza said the Arizona Constitution requires initiative campaigns to collect signatures from supporters in person.
The state Supreme Court may still weigh in on the issue in a similar lawsuit filed by other ballot measure campaigns.
One campaign behind the case in state court is aiming to get a question on the ballot legalizing the use of recreational marijuana.